reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very good quality.
reviews.reviewText: Sturdy, well made. Great pockets for organization. Not lightweight. Thick heavy leather. A little heavy for me but I am keeping because quality is excellent and classic style. My laptop fits perfectly and still enough room for more. 👍

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 26, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Stylish and practical
reviews.reviewText: This bag worked great for my most recent business trip. I was able to fit 2 laptops, all of their accessories and some personal items as well. The color is beautiful and I received plenty of compliments. I even shared the purchase info with a stranger as we entered into the plane. Only downside is that the bag is heavy without much in it due to quality material; therefore at capacity it is pretty weighty. Still 5 stars for me.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very nice bag
reviews.reviewText: The green one is so pretty.Pros: I like that the laptop sits in the middle. It will stand up as long as the weight is balanced. It appears well made. Lots of pockets. Holds all my cords and battery bank with lots of room left.Cons: Its heavy, there's one zipper compartment, its held together with magnetic buttons so the whole thing does not close.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars I'm always looking for the perfect bag.
reviews.reviewText: I'm always on the lookout for the perfect bag because I carry a lot of STUFF. Lately a laptop has been added to this amount so I needed a bag that could accommodate both my personal and my business "stuff". I love the exterior tooled leather look and I picked the green. To me, it looks like an expensive bag! I love the sturdiness and the fact that it doesn't collapse in a heap making it easy to find what I need without empting all the contents. The straps can be lengthened to a persons taste. It holds my laptop and power cords plus the other "stuff" I mentioned and the three inner partitions stay upright and don't sag. The center is a zip pocket. The magnetic closures work well unless you overstuff. The only "con" I've seen is it's a little heavy even when it's empty. This may be the trade off for the durability so I can handle that. Bottom line is....this bag is about as close as I've come to perfect but I'm still not giving it 5 stars but I would give it 4.5 if I could!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great value, roomy and stylish
reviews.reviewText: I bought this to use as my work bag and it’s fantastic. The color is beautiful and it seems pretty high quality but is very affordable. I was surprised how much you can fit into this bag - laptop (I have my MacBook Pro in mine), notebook, to-go makeup bag, phone, wallet, and a few more misc items.The middle has a zipper pocket for your laptop and there are multiple other smaller pockets inside.Versatile, affordable, and looks great!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 13, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Extremely cute bag. I needed a laptop bag that wasn’t one of those ugly black ones to carry my laptop, water bottle, lunch, and notebook back and forth to work. This bag is great. I love that it’s “leather” and won’t stain like many of the similar canvas bags for sale today. Stands up on its own and zips nicely. The metal snaps are strong and clasp tightly.(Minor) Cons- I do wish it had a key straps so they don’t get lost in the bottom and one of the matching bags you can put smaller items in but I have one I can throw in instead.Overall a fantastic bag!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Just what I was looking for to carry my laptop and other teacher necessities. Sturdy handles and beautiful color. Love the divided areas inside which allows me to organize my things.

Bought it for school books and laptop compartment. Looks great, stands up on its own, has metal legs so it doesn't actually touch the ground.I was debating between the brown vs. black but the colour is just like photo.

reviews.reviewTitle: Really spacious bag which surprisingly doesn't feel very clunky or filled
reviews.reviewText: I researched a lot before buying this bag and initially I was skeptical because any bag you buy for 15.6'' laptop either ends up looking tooo bulky and filled OR doesn't have enough space for all your other items post laptopSurprisingly, this bag was a dream. U can put laptop in the middle and it still has 2 more even bigger pockets for all your things.It doesn't feel too bulky or filled.Overall loved it. Worth buying
I love how every thing I have has it’s own spot in the bag and I can find things easier. Easy to carry and is stylish. I am very happy with this bag!!
The only thing about this bag is that the straps are starting to crack at the seams. I have only had it for a few weeks and I do not overload it.
